        "text": "1 Corinthians 5:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " shows us how they would “keep the Feast”. Ramsay’s “fixed date in the life of St. Paul,” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Expositor",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", May, 1896, depends partly on the assumption that Paul left Philippi the very first day after the close of the Paschal week, but we cannot be sure of this, see Wendt’s criticism on Ramsay’s view, p. 326, edition 1899, and also Dr. Robertson “I. Corinthians” Hastings’ B.D., p. 485.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἄχρις ἡμ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πέντε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": “in five days,” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
