        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the journey lasted until the fifth day, so ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πεμπταῖοι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "cf.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "δευτεραῖοι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 28:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 16:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the journey only lasted two (three?) days, but here probably adverse winds must be taken into account; or the five days may include a delay at Neapolis, the port of Philippi, or the land journey to the port; on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἄχρις",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " see above ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 1:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἡμέρας ἑπτά",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", so as to include a whole week, and so the first day of the week, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "cf.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Corinthians 2:12-13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which shows how reluctantly Paul left Troas on his former visit, but see on the other hand, Ramsay, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "St. Paul",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", p. 295, who thinks that St. Paul would not have voluntarily stayed seven days at Troas.",
